About 4 months ago, me and a friend we're playing our lower levels.  I was level 29 rogue and my friend was level 30ish monk.  We pulled a wolf near the lake camp by Griegs end in DS and the #$*&amp;ing NPCS there aggroed and wiped us out.  I say's to myself okay.  Logged on with our high levels and I paused....Okay level 61 mobs, four of them.  I said what the hell and pulled one off split it from the others and we got down to buisiness, Hit for 170s, pretty quickly, stunned every 3-4 hits and had lots of hps but we kicked its ass.  Not much exp but we had the satisfaction of payback.<br>
<br>
Over the months I would come back and teach a refresher course every so often, just so they would never forget.  When the talk began of the Exp changed, I stayed silent....Waiting.  The change went live and I Pounced.  With a 60 monk, 60 cleric, 53 wizard in the group every kill netted me (60 monk) a 1/3 of a blue AA.  It took about 3-5 min per kill, about 1 min between fights (mostly to split the mobs, 6 min respawn time on 2 of the 4 mobs).  Needless to say I kept this quiet and just amongst the guild.<br>
<br>
I log on just a little while ago and guess what?  The mobs are now light blue with infinite hit points (or a regen so strong might as well be infinite).<br>
<br>
